request.description:
### GET /user

This endpoint retrieves a list of users with the ability to paginate and order the results.

#### Request

- Method: GET

- URL: {{BaseUrl}}user/

- Query Parameters:

    - page (integer, optional): The page number for pagination.

    - page_size (integer, optional): The number of items per page.

    - ordering (string, optional): The field to use for ordering the results. Prefix with '-' for descending order.

    - Ordering by :-

    - username, created_at


#### Response

The response is a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "status": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "username": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "email": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "phone_number": {
            "type": ["string", "null"]
          },
          "first_name": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "middle_name": {
            "type": ["string", "null"]
          },
          "last_name": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "role_id": {
            "type": ["string", "null"]
          },
          "organization_id": {
            "type": ["string", "null"]
          },
          "full_name": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "required": ["id", "username", "email", "first_name", "last_name", "full_name"]
      }
    }
  },
  "required": ["status", "message", "data"]
}

 ```

The response contains a boolean status, an optional message, and an array of user objects with their respective properties.

